<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I traded a Blade of Xalgoz, Jarsath Battle Sword, and Exe axe for this 2hb. I think it was worth it. the proc does 30 damage, but procs like crazy. My friend (with 20 skill) got it to proc 7 times in one fight with me the other day. </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kragmire</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-16 16:33:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well, a shammy can finally fight a little now :)<BR>
<BR>
Got this thing on my level 49 shammy and it kicks.  Have other wisdom items that I use when casting, but when I wade into melee I shift to this.  No kidding, but I have hit for 99 damage AS WELL AS have the proc go off in one round.  Not shabby at all for a shaman.  Toss in a shammy's ability to self-buff STR, DEX and SPEED, and you can start to outdamage your pet again :)  Course you'll never be a tank, but hell it's nice to know you can deal out 500 or more melee damage when the s**t hits the fan.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
